BARD COMBAT

Bard combat is about tempo. You are strongest when you keep a song field active,
vary song forms, build Performance, and choose the right Finale when the fight
turns in your favor.

Basic combat rhythm:

  1. Start with a field.
     pulsebeat, emberaria, silververse, echochord, dirgeash, or ashlullaby.

  2. Vary your form.
     Repeating one song over and over builds less Performance than moving
     between Rhythm, Melody, Harmony, and Dissonance. These forms use separate
     cooldowns, so changing forms is also much faster than repeating one form.

  3. Watch Performance.
     Use bscore or bmon. High Performance opens stronger moments. Charisma
     improves Performance gain, field force, field duration, and hidden harmony
     payoff.

  4. Use Crescendo and Finale.
     apexchord can help push toward a finishing moment. echoburst,
     battlefieldsilence, and Wail spend that moment in different ways. When
     bscore or bmon says Finale is ready, spend it quickly.

  5. Study the fight.
     study can show emotional resonance. soothe, otto, and morale pressure can
     change the shape of the room without being simple damage.

  6. Match the moment.
     Archetype, instrument, active fields, hidden patterns, Performance, and
     Charisma now all feed into Bard command strength. A Doom Singer with a
     violin and Dissonance already hanging in the room should feel different
     from a War Conductor with drums and Harmony carrying the party.

Core battle commands:

  pulsebeat          Rhythm timing support.
  emberaria          Melody steadiness support.
  silververse        Melody healing support.
  echochord          Harmony timing support.
  dirgeash           Dissonance enemy pressure.
  ashlullaby         Dissonance mesmerize pressure.
  soothe             Calm combat in the room.
  hero               Heroic role song.
  villain            Villainous role song.
  whispercanticle    Flute song that clouds enemy focus.
  mirrorrefrain      Chimes song that disrupts enemy timing.
  apexchord          Crescendo for high Performance.
  echoburst          Finale that bursts active fields.
  muse               Harmony inspiration field.
  battlefieldsilence Finale that disrupts enemies.
  otto               Force a target to dance.
  rally              Courage and mental resilience.
  ssing              Create a singing sword.
  Wail               Banshee Finale.

Tips:

  Keep bmon on while learning.
  Use bcmds to see cooldown time and cooldown family.
  Use bardhelp songs to understand forms and hidden harmonies.
  Use bardhelp instruments before deciding which instrument to carry.
  Use bardhelp archetypes before choosing specialize at guild level 10.
  Raise Charisma if you want your performances to matter more.
